lives of citizens. The new American political economy, it is argued, needs to be understood as composed of a mosaic of urban experiences that both build upon a differentiated foundation and creates new divergences. As state reforms continue to interact with this diverse urban political economy of the United States, this collection provides a state-of-the-art survey on how postcrisis convergences and divergences in urban economies and urban politics have laid the foundations for the new political geography of the United States.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aFiscal crisiszUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aMunicipal budgetszUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aMunicipal governmentzUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Environmental Studies. 4aPolitics and Law : American Government. 4aPolitics and Law : American Politics. 4aPublic Policy : Urban and Regional Planning. 4aSociology : Urban Sociology. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / City Planning & Urban Development.2bisacsh1 aBolton, Chalem, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChen, Xueying, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavidson, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavidson, Mark, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHammel, Daniel J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHinkley, Sara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKirkpatrick, L. Owen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNewman, Kathe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNiznik, Aaron, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeck, Jamie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.l